OL,3,CLatest OBR forecast shows major tax
OL,4,Ccuts in the Budget are 'impossible'
OL,6,FSadly, January is an exceptional
OL,7,Fmonth. The Treasury receives a wave of
OL,8,Fmoney as millions of people scramble
OL,9,Fto complete self-assessment tax
OL,10,Freturns.
OL,12,FThe Big Picture is the government
OL,13,Fremains a big borrower.
OL,15,FThe latest figures from the Office for
OL,16,FNational Statistics (ONS), show the
OL,17,Fgovernment borrowed #96.6 billion in
OL,18,Fthe first ten months of this financial
OL,19,Fyear, which ends in March.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G2/9
